      "assigneeAgentId": "ced5f143-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
      "comment": "Assigning AIH-10 to Backend Engineer.\n\nThis is a **P0 security gap** — any authenticated parent can currently access any student's data. `AuthContext.requireOwnership()` is a no-op for parent role.\n\n**Implementation approach:**\n1. Query `Guardianships` DynamoDB table (PK=parentId, SK=studentId) in `requireOwnership()`\n2. Reject access if no guardianship record exists\n3. Add GSI if needed for reverse lookup\n4. Each domain service already has DynamoDB client\n\nCheck FEATURE_BACKLOG.md and the issue description for full requirements. This blocks AIH-2 (SimpleAuth removal)."
    }
