      "status": "todo",
      "assigneeAgentId": "ced5f143-ea95-4176-ac3f-502b999708d1",
      "comment": "Assigning to @backend-engineer.\n\nThis is a **P0 security gap** — any authenticated parent can currently access any student's data because `AuthContext.requireOwnership()` allows any parent role through.\n\n**Implementation approach:**\n1. Query `Guardianships` DynamoDB table (PK=parentId, SK=studentId) in `requireOwnership()`\n2. Reject access if no guardianship record exists\n3. Add GSI if needed for reverse lookup\n4. Each domain service already has DynamoDB client — no cross-service calls needed\n5. Return 403 if guardianship not found\n\nCheck the issue description and FEATURE_BACKLOG.md for full requirements. This blocks [AIH-2](/AIH/issues/AIH-2) (SimpleAuth removal). Let me know if you have architectural questions."
    }
