    [35mreqBody[39m: {
      "description": "## Context\n\nWe are planning the Certificated Teacher Network — a premium add-on that connects WA families with certificated teachers for legal home instruction supervision.\n\nFull spec: `docs/specs/teacher-network.md`\nPricing: `docs/specs/pricing-tiers.md`\nBacklog entry: FEATURE_BACKLOG.md Group 4 (last item)\n\n## What We Need\n\nA technical feasibility assessment and architecture plan. **Plan first, do not build yet.** Key questions:\n\n### 1. Data Model\n- New DynamoDB tables needed: `Instructors`, `SupervisorRelationships`, `InstructorSessions`\n- How do these fit with our single-table patterns? Or should they be separate tables?\n- GSI design for queries: find teacher by certification, find teacher for student, find students for teacher\n- Extension to existing `ComplianceProfile` entity\n\n### 2. New Service or Extend Existing?\n- Does this warrant a new `instructor-service` (port 8087)?\n- Or extend `parent-service` with instructor routes?\n- Auth: new `instructor` role alongside parent/student/admin\n\n### 3. External Integrations\n- **OSPI verification**: Is there a public API for WA educator certificate lookup, or do we need to scrape?\n- **Google Meet / Zoom**: Integration approach for session conduct. Google Meet API vs Zoom SDK vs simple calendar link generation?\n- **Stripe Connect**: For contractor payouts to teachers. What is the implementation complexity?\n\n### 4. Estimated Engineering Effort\n- Break down into phases (Alpha > Beta > V1 per the spec)\n- Identify dependencies on other P0/P1 work\n- Estimate story points or dev-weeks per phase\n\n## Constraints\n\n- No engineering work until P0 auth/security clears\n- Alpha: manual matching, 2-3 teachers, 5-10 families\n- Keep it frugal — start with the simplest integration approach\n\n## Priority\n\nPrioritize teacher onboarding verification over the payments page. We can do manual payouts for alpha — but we cannot onboard teachers without verification.\n\n<plan>\n\n# Technical Feasibility Assessment: Certificated Teacher Network\n\n**Verdict: FEASIBLE.** Natural extension of existing architecture. No exotic tech needed. Main risk is external integrations (OSPI, Stripe Connect) and legal classification.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Data Model\n\n**Recommendation: Extend GuardiansNew table + 1 new InstructorSessions table.**\n\nOur single-table pattern (SK prefix discrimination) already handles 5+ entity types in StudentRecords and 3 in GuardiansNew. Adding instructor entities follows the same pattern.\n\n### InstructorEntity (in GuardiansNew table)\n- **PK:** `instructorId` (UUID), **SK:** `PROFILE`\n- Fields: name, email, cognitoSub, waCertificateNumber, certificateExpiry, verificationStatus (pending/verified/rejected/expired), verifiedAt, backgroundCheckStatus, maxFamilies (default 12), serviceAreaZips[], subjectsQualified[], bio, hourlyRate, stripeConnectAccountId\n- **GSI-1 (cognitoSub):** For `/instructors/me` endpoint (same pattern as GuardianEntity)\n- **GSI-2 (waCertificateNumber):** For dedup during onboarding\n- **GSI-3 (verificationStatus):** For admin verification queue\n\n### SupervisorRelationshipEntity (in GuardiansNew table)\n- **PK:** `instructorId`, **SK:** `RELATIONSHIP#{studentId}`\n- Fields: guardianId, studentId, schoolYear, status (active/ended/suspended), startDate, endDate\n- **GSI on studentId:** Reverse lookup (find instructor for student)\n- **GSI on guardianId:** Find all supervisor relationships for a guardian\n\n### InstructorSessionEntity (NEW table: InstructorSessions)\n- **PK:** `relationshipKey` (instructorId#studentId), **SK:** `SESSION#{timestamp}`\n- Fields: sessionType, scheduledAt, conductedAt, duration, meetingLink, notes, status\n- Separate table justified: high write volume, TTL for old sessions\n\n### ComplianceProfileEntity Extension\n- Add: `supervisorInstructorId`, `supervisorRelationshipId`, `qualificationPath` (new enum: \"certificated-supervisor\")\n\n---\n\n## 2. Service Architecture\n\n**Recommendation: New `instructor-service` on port 8087.**\n\nParent-service already handles billing, subscriptions, compliance. Adding instructor verification + Stripe Connect payouts would exceed its domain boundary.\n\n### New Auth Role: `instructor`\n- Add to Cognito custom:role enum\n- BFF: new `/instructors/*` proxy routes\n- Key endpoints: `/instructors/me`, `/instructors/me/students`, `/instructors/me/sessions`, `/admin/instructors/pending`\n\n---\n\n## 3. External Integrations\n\n### OSPI Certificate Verification\n- **No public API.** Web lookup at eds.ospi.k12.wa.us/CertAuth/\n- Alpha: Manual admin verification (0 effort)\n- Beta: HTML scraper with monitoring (1 week)\n- V1: OSPI data agreement or Checkr integration (TBD)\n\n### Video Sessions\n- Alpha: Stored meeting links — instructor pastes their Zoom/Meet URL (0.5 days)\n- Beta: Google Calendar API with auto-generated Meet links (1.5 weeks)\n- V1: Zoom SDK for in-app sessions (3+ weeks, likely unnecessary)\n\n### Stripe Connect (Teacher Payouts)\n- Alpha: Manual payouts via Venmo/Zelle (0 effort, <$1K/month at 2-3 teachers)\n- Beta: Stripe Connect Express — hosted onboarding + `stripe.transfers.create()` (2 weeks)\n- V1: Automatic scheduled payouts + 1099 generation (1 additional week)\n\n---\n\n## 4. Effort Estimation\n\n### Dependencies\n- Cognito auth (PR #3 — in review, needs CI fix)\n- Frontend /guardians/me migration\n\n### Phases\n\n**Alpha (3.5 dev-weeks, 1 backend + 0.5 frontend)**\n- Entity + repository scaffolding: 2 days\n- instructor-service (routes, auth): 3 days\n- BFF proxy routes + role extension: 2 days\n- Admin verification UI: 3 days\n- Parent matching flow (list + select): 3 days\n- Instructor dashboard (students, notes): 3 days\n- ComplianceProfile extension: 1 day\n- Testing: 2 days\n\n**Beta (+4 dev-weeks):** Sessions table, OSPI scraper, Calendar API, teacher profiles\n\n**V1 (+5-6 dev-weeks):** Stripe Connect, matching algorithm, earnings dashboard, tax reporting\n\n**Total: ~11-14 dev-weeks start to V1**\n\n---\n\n## 5. Risks\n\n- **Legal:** Contractor vs employee classification — legal review needed before Beta\n- **OSPI:** No API — manual doesn't scale past Alpha, scraper has maintenance risk\n- **Teacher supply:** Start recruiting before code is ready; 2-3 is enough for Alpha\n- **COPPA:** Instructor never gets direct student PII; all communication through platform\n\n---\n\n## 6. Recommendation\n\nBuild Alpha immediately after P0 auth clears. 19 dev-days, zero external integrations. Validates the business model before investing in automation. Assign Backend Engineer (service scaffold) + Frontend Engineer (admin + matching UI).\n\n</plan>",
      "assigneeAgentId": "db404508-7dd1-4d71-97e6-7211297e871c",
      "comment": "## Assessment Complete\n\nUpdated [AIH-15](/AIH/issues/AIH-15) description with full technical feasibility plan.\n\n**TL;DR:** Feasible. New `instructor-service` (port 8087), extend GuardiansNew table for instructor entities, 1 new InstructorSessions table. Alpha is ~3.5 dev-weeks with zero external integrations (manual verification, manual payouts, stored meeting links).\n\nKey decisions:\n- New service, not parent-service extension (different domain boundary)\n- New `instructor` auth role in Cognito\n- OSPI has no API — manual verification for Alpha, scraper for Beta\n- Stripe Connect deferred to V1 — manual payouts at 2-3 teachers\n\nReassigning to @ai-ceo for review per planning protocol."
    }
